    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    probability.classifier_name='lc_classifier'

) AS sq1
  INNER JOIN (
SELECT
    object.oid, probability.probability
FROM
    object INNER JOIN
    probability
    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    probability.classifier_name='lc_classifier'
    AND probability.class_name='CV/Nova'

) as sq2

     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.ranking = 1 ),
     filtered_objects AS
  (-- Filter objects with more than 50 detections
 SELECT o.oid
   FROM OBJECT o
   WHERE o.ndet > 50 ),
     candidate_ids AS
  (-- Get candidate IDs for objects in filtered_objects
 SELECT d.candid,
        d.oid,
        d.mjd,
        d.fid,
        d.magpsf,
        d.sigmapsf,
        d.ra,
        d.dec
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM filtered_objects) ),
     light_curve_stats AS
  (-- Calculate initial rise estimate and rate for each object and band
 SELECT c.oid,
        c.candid,
        c.mjd,
        c.fid,
        c.magpsf,
        c.sigmapsf,
        c.ra,
        c.dec, -- Get first detection time per object and band
 FIRST_VALUE(c.mjd) OVER (PARTITION BY c.oid,
                                       c.fid
                          ORDER BY c.mjd) AS first_mjd, -- Get first detection magnitude per object and band
 FIRST_VALUE(c.magpsf) OVER (PARTITION BY c.oid,
                                          c.fid
                             ORDER BY c.mjd) AS first_mag, -- Get last detection time per object and band
 LAST_VALUE(c.mjd) OVER (PARTITION BY c.oid,
                                      c.fid
                         ORDER BY c.mjd ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING) AS last_mjd, -- Get last detection magnitude per object and band
 LAST_VALUE(c.magpsf) OVER (PARTITION BY c.oid,
                                         c.fid
                            ORDER BY c.mjd ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING) AS last_mag
   FROM candidate_ids c),
     rise_rates AS
  (-- Calculate initial rise rate (mag/day) for each object and band
 SELECT oid,
        candid,
        first_mjd,
        last_mjd,
        first_mag,
        last_mag, -- Avoid division by zero
 CASE
     WHEN (last_mjd - first_mjd) > 0 THEN (last_mag - first_mag) / (last_mjd - first_mjd)
     ELSE NULL
 END AS rise_rate
   FROM light_curve_stats),
     final_objects AS
  (-- Filter objects with rise rate > 0.5 mag/day
 SELECT DISTINCT o.oid

  detection.candid, detection.fid as f_id,detection.magpsf, detection.sigmapsf_corr, detection.sigmapsf_corr_ext
FROM
  (
SELECT

FROM

SELECT
  magstat.oid, magstat.fid, magstat.dmdt_first
FROM
  (
SELECT
    object.oid
FROM

    probability
    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    probability.classifier_name='lc_classifier'
    AND probability.class_name='SNII'
    AND probability.probability > 0.6
    AND object.ndet > 30
) as obj_oids
    INNER JOIN
    magstat ON magstat.oid = obj_oids.oid
WHERE
  magstat.dmdt_first < -0.5
  AND (magstat.fid = 1 OR magstat.fid = 2)
) as obj_oids_fast
    INNER JOIN
    magstat ON magstat.oid = obj_oids_fast.oid
WHERE
  magstat.lastmjd > 100 + magstat.firstmjd
  AND magstat.fid = 2
) AS sq
  INNER JOIN detection
  ON sq.oid = detection.oid
WHERE
  detection.mjd > 58484.0
  AND detection.mjd < 59944.0
ORDER BY oid

WITH sn_ii_objects AS

   FROM OBJECT o
   JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
   WHERE p.class_name = 'SNII'
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN 58484.0 AND 59944.0 ),
     sn_ii_detections AS
  (SELECT d.candid,
          d.oid,
          d.mjd,
          d.magpsf,
          d.sigmapsf,
          d.fid AS f_id
   FROM detection d
   JOIN sn_ii_objects o ON d.oid = o.oid),
     rise_rates AS
  (SELECT d1.oid,
          (d2.magpsf - d1.magpsf) / (d2.mjd - d1.mjd) AS rise_rate,
          d1.mjd AS start_mjd,
          d2.mjd AS end_mjd
   FROM sn_ii_detections d1
   JOIN sn_ii_detections d2 ON d1.oid = d2.oid
   AND d2.mjd > d1.mjd
   WHERE d1.f_id IN (1,
                     2)
     AND d2.f_id IN (1,
                     2) ),
     initial_rise AS
  (SELECT oid,
          AVG(rise_rate) AS avg_rise_rate
   FROM rise_rates

   GROUP BY oid),
     observation_stats AS
  (SELECT d.oid,
          COUNT(*) FILTER (
                           WHERE d.f_id = 2) AS r_band_detections,
          COUNT(*) AS total_detections
   FROM sn_ii_detections d

       d.sigmapsf,

JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
JOIN initial_rise ir ON o.oid = ir.oid
JOIN observation_stats os ON o.oid = os.oid

  (SELECT ms.oid,

          ms.magmean,
          ms.sigmadm_first,
          ms.dmdt_first,

  (SELECT oid,
          f_id, -- Calculate initial rise rate: change in magnitude over time

     ELSE NULL

     (SELECT DISTINCT oid,

   LEFT JOIN detection_filtered d2 ON m.oid = d2.oid
   AND m.f_id = d2.f_id
   AND d2.mjd > d1.mjd
   WHERE d1.mjd IS NOT NULL
     AND d2.mjd IS NOT NULL ),
     objects_with_rise AS
  (SELECT DISTINCT oid
   FROM rise_rates
   WHERE rise_rate > 0.5 ),
     detection_final AS
  (SELECT d.candid,
          d.oid,
          d.mjd,
          d.magpsf,
          d.sigmapsf,

WITH sn_ii_objects AS

          p.probability,
          d.candid,
          d.mjd,

          d.sigmapsf,
          d.fid AS band_id,
          d.ra,
          d.dec
   FROM OBJECT o

   JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oid
   WHERE p.class_name = 'SNII'
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND d.mjd BETWEEN 58484.0 AND 59944.0 ), -- Filter objects with sufficient r-band observations and detections
filtered_objects AS
  (SELECT oid
   FROM sn_ii_objects
   WHERE band_id = 2 -- r-band

   GROUP BY oid
   HAVING COUNT(*) >= 100
   AND COUNT(DISTINCT candid) > 30), -- Calculate initial rise rate for each object in g and r bands
rise_rates AS
  (SELECT o.oid, -- For each object, find the earliest and latest detection in g-band
 MIN(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.mjd
     END) AS g_start_mjd,
 MAX(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.mjd
     END) AS g_end_mjd, -- For r-band
 MIN(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.mjd
     END) AS r_start_mjd,
 MAX(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.mjd
     END) AS r_end_mjd, -- Corresponding magnitudes
 MIN(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.magpsf
     END) AS g_min_mag,
 MIN(CASE
         WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.magpsf
     END) AS r_min_mag
   FROM OBJECT o
   JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oid
   WHERE o.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM filtered_objects)
   GROUP BY o.oid), -- Calculate rise rates in mag/day for g and r bands
rise_rate_calc AS

              WHEN g_end_mjd IS NOT NULL
                   AND g_start_mjd IS NOT NULL
                   AND (g_end_mjd - g_start_mjd) > 0 THEN (g_min_mag -
                                                             (SELECT MIN(magpsf)
                                                              FROM detection
                                                              WHERE oid = o.oid
                                                                AND fid = 1
                                                                AND mjd BETWEEN g_start_mjd AND g_end_mjd)) / (g_end_mjd - g_start_mjd)
              ELSE NULL
          END AS g_rise_rate,
          CASE
              WHEN r_end_mjd IS NOT NULL
                   AND r_start_mjd IS NOT NULL
                   AND (r_end_mjd - r_start_mjd) > 0 THEN (r_min_mag -
                                                             (SELECT MIN(magpsf)
                                                              FROM detection
                                                              WHERE oid = o.oid
                                                                AND fid = 2
                                                                AND mjd BETWEEN r_start_mjd AND r_end_mjd)) / (r_end_mjd - r_start_mjd)
